races.nyt_race_description: Senator Kelly Loeffler, who was appointed to her seat in 2019 and is seeking to finish a term that ends in 2022, is vying against the Rev. Raphael Warnock, who leads Ebenezer Baptist Church in Atlanta. In November’s crowded special election, Mr. Warnock finished with 32.9 percent of the vote and Ms. Loeffler had 25.9 percent.
races.poll_display: Polls closed at 7 p.m. Eastern time.
